HEADWORD: Hyoglossus
<hw>Hy`o*glos"sus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
<ets>hyo-</ets> hyo- + Gr. <grk>glw^ssa</grk> tongue.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A flat muscle on either side of the tongue,
connecting it with the hyoid bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

